First Kenyan Attorney-General and the last member of the Kenyan first Cabinet of Ministers, Sir Charles Njonjo has died aged 101, Kenya's President Uhuru Kenyatta announced on Sunday. He died on Sunday, January 2, at his home in Muthaiga, Nairobi, his family says. Njonjo succumbed to pneumonia. His body was, thereafter, taken to Lee Funeral Home, where it was prepared for interment. Njonjoâ€™s family then proceeded to Kariokor Hindu Crematorium, where the former Attorney-General was cremated in the morning.